summary:
So I hit 600 followers yesterday and idk it may not seem like much but it's a pretty big milestone for me.
I thought I'd do...
body:
So I hit 600 followers yesterday and idk it may not seem like much but it’s a pretty big milestone for me.

I thought I’d do something to celebrate it but I didn’t know what, exactly. But now I have an idea, and I’d really appreciate it if you guys wanted this too:

I was thinking that you could send me stuff you’d like me to write (Marvel, preferably, but not only limited to it. I can do crossovers like the John Wick thing, too, as long as I’m familiar with the other thing you want me to integrate).

I’ve never done this kinda thing before, but I’d like to give it a shot.

The only “rules” for this are that you should be following me, preferably, and idk maybe you could reblog this for others to see?

I’m waiting for your requests, no matter how ridiculous, odd or whatever they are!

@olkoye @magic-metal @supremehusbands @bit-chalky @thecooingcat @ironmanstan @armoredsoftie I’m tagging you because most of you guys have way more followers than I do and this bitch needs promoting sorry

summary: So I'm having an innocent dream...
body:
So I’m having an innocent dream…

Everything in my dream is playing out accordingly: I have a boy out of my league hitting on me, we’re around the occasional random celebrity, and I’m living my best life.

In said dream I’m talking to a dude I’ve had a crush on for a while who I’m about to kiss, and suddenly he turns to fucking ash in front of me.

I turn around and notice Hugh Jackman drop while Ryan Reynolds looks distraught. Tom Holland appears and just as quickly dissapears.

I immediately know its Thanos, and I’m pissed. But in my horny dream state all I can think/say is “why is Thanos such a fucking cockblock”

Ryan Reynolds was not amused.

I immediately woke up angry, confused, and for .2 seconds thought that the whole Thanos thing happened irl.

summary: Okay, I just finished watching Infinity War here in the comfort of my own bed and...
body:
Okay, I just finished watching Infinity War here in the comfort of my own bed and…

  1. Thor watching Loki die still sucks massive balls. Thanks for that Russo brothers.
  2. Doctor Strange winking at Tony and Tony smirking as he walks away? Amazing! And I didn’t notice that when I saw it in theaters.
  3. Bruce and Tony geeking out over Tony’s new upgrades in the midst of an alien invasion, cute. Note taken for possible implementation in fic.
  4. “I don’t want another pop culture reference outta you for the rest of the trip.” My family to me.
  5. Ariana Greenblatt, who plays young Gamora is amazing! The little twitches and small facial changes really sell her as a young Gamora.
  6. Peter catching the Guardians on Titan and then apologizing about not being able to remember their names is me when new people start at my place of work.
  7. I’m convinced that young Gamora asking Thanos if he did it and what it cost IS inside the soul stone. And because that’s how he sees her (“little one”) that’s how she manifests. The disappointment on her face when she finds out he did it has to be in real time.

I’m skipping to the end now because I got sucked into the movies and didn’t take notes. Next time.

8. When we get to the after credits scene we arrive with Maria Hill and Nick Fury talking in the SUV. Listening to their conversation, Maria Hill says something about several bogeys flying in over Wakanda, about them being bigger than New York, and then the oncoming vehicle crashes which means that the snap happened and shortly after she disappears, as does Fury. It happens so quickly. So what I make of this is A. Someone else is flying in over Wakanda. Something or someone else? B. And I think this is much more likely, the sequence was made to (yes, obviously tease Captain Marvel) simply show the Snap from a different and other perspective. More real world and less battle field.

  5. Ariana Greenblatt, who plays young Gamora is amazing! The little twitches and small facial changes really sell her as a young Gamora.
  6. Peter catching the Guardians on Titan and then apologizing about not being able to remember their names is me when new people start at my place of work.
  7. I’m convinced that young Gamora asking Thanos if he did it and what it cost IS inside the soul stone. And because that’s how he sees her (“little one”) that’s how she manifests. The disappointment on her face when she finds out he did it has to be in real time.

I’m skipping to the end now because I got sucked into the movies and didn’t take notes. Next time.

8. When we get to the after credits scene we arrive with Maria Hill and Nick Fury talking in the SUV. Listening to their conversation, Maria Hill says something about several bogeys flying in over Wakanda, about them being bigger than New York, and then the oncoming vehicle crashes which means that the snap happened and shortly after she disappears, as does Fury. It happens so quickly. So what I make of this is A. Someone else is flying in over Wakanda. Something or someone else? B. And I think this is much more likely, the sequence was made to (yes, obviously tease Captain Marvel) simply show the Snap from a different and other perspective. More real world and less battle field.
